parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or seize, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine seizes or stalls
smoke comes from the engine compartment
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle loses power
and the engine makes a knocking or flapping noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine knocking or bearing failure can cause the engine to seize or stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine makes a knocking or flapping noise
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle loses power
and the engine oil pressure warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle is subject to a recall
but the parts are not available
or the repair is delayed
leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to slow down or stop unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to slow down or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to properly respond upon acceleration
the engine stalls or loses power
the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving recall repairs can cause drivers to continue operating their vehicles with known safety defects, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The contact received notification of the recall
but the parts to complete the repair are not yet available
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and idling issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to a loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine light comes on
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering becomes difficult
the engine idles low
the vehicle takes time to accelerate
the vehicle stalls while driving
and the vehicle shuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spontaneous shattering of glass can cause injury to occupants, especially if the glass falls into the vehicle. This can also lead to a loss of control while driving.
symptoms: The panoramic sunroof or rear glass shatters suddenly
without any apparent cause
while driving or parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of components such as the compressor and clutch can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The compressor blows out
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.
